{
  "text": "Since D is a diagonal matrix, exp(tD) is also a diagonal matrix whose i-th diagonal element is exp(tD ii ). In contrast to the diffusion kernel where the task is to predict the characteristics of the data in a network-structured feature space, we can consider the different problem of predicting the external structure (meaning the network structure) from the given feature spaces. In that case, the task is to predict pair-wise relationships (such as the existence of links) among data. The pair-wise kernel [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] is can be used for such purposes. Let us denote byK a kernel matrix defined by a given feature space. Then the pair-wise kernel K is defined as",
